WEBVTT - https://maestrasuite.com

0
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:08.509
Friends, this block is
especially important if

1
00:00:08.520 --> 00:00:11.329
your child has difficulties
with reading, writing,

2
00:00:11.340 --> 00:00:12.259
or concentration.

3
00:00:12.940 --> 00:00:16.469
At first glance, it may seem
like this is about studying,

4
00:00:16.480 --> 00:00:19.309
but in fact, everything
begins with the body, with

5
00:00:19.320 --> 00:00:22.609
coordination, cross-body
movements, and the ability

6
00:00:22.620 --> 00:00:23.709
to maintain balance.

7
00:00:24.400 --> 00:00:28.548
In these exercises, we will
combine movement, attention,

8
00:00:28.560 --> 00:00:31.929
and control, and that
is exactly what creates

9
00:00:31.940 --> 00:00:34.019
the foundation for
easier learning.

10
00:00:34.460 --> 00:00:37.749
The format remains playful,
but the effect goes far beyond

11
00:00:37.760 --> 00:00:39.879
simple physical activity.

12
00:00:39.920 --> 00:00:40.519
Let's begin.

13
00:00:43.640 --> 00:00:45.799
I absolutely love
this exercise.

14
00:00:45.920 --> 00:00:47.419
Children love it too.

15
00:00:47.450 --> 00:00:48.089
Don't rush.

16
00:00:48.480 --> 00:00:51.599
Over time, it will start
to work better and better.

17
00:00:51.680 --> 00:00:52.779
So what do we do?

18
00:00:52.820 --> 00:00:55.829
We bounce a tennis ball on
the floor with the right hand,

19
00:00:55.840 --> 00:00:58.429
catch it with the left hand,
pass it back to the right,

20
00:00:58.440 --> 00:01:00.059
and repeat several times.

21
00:01:00.120 --> 00:01:02.459
Then we switch hands
and do it the other way.

22
00:01:02.500 --> 00:01:04.318
Do ten repetitions
for each hand.

23
00:01:04.700 --> 00:01:06.829
If it is difficult for
the child at first,

24
00:01:06.840 --> 00:01:08.319
do fewer repetitions.

25
00:01:44.620 --> 00:01:47.989
At the beginning in this
exercise, the child needs to

26
00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:51.629
simultaneously stretch their
arms forward, holding a ball

27
00:01:51.640 --> 00:01:54.389
or toy, and straighten the
bent leg at the hip and

28
00:01:54.400 --> 00:01:57.279
knee joints, then return
to the starting position.

29
00:01:57.700 --> 00:01:59.948
It would be great if you
can do ten repetitions

30
00:01:59.960 --> 00:02:00.579
on each leg.

31
00:02:00.980 --> 00:02:03.619
And as usual, don't forget
to enjoy the process.

32
00:04:18.640 --> 00:04:21.838
Make a straight line on the
floor several meters long.

33
00:04:21.899 --> 00:04:23.659
You can draw it
or stretch a rope.

34
00:04:24.250 --> 00:04:26.419
Scatter small objects
around the line.

35
00:04:27.000 --> 00:04:30.349
At the beginning of the game,
the child stands on the line,

36
00:04:30.360 --> 00:04:33.169
one foot directly in front
of the other, holding any

37
00:04:33.180 --> 00:04:35.919
container that can be used to
collect the scattered objects.

38
00:04:36.510 --> 00:04:39.349
The child walks along the
line, placing one foot

39
00:04:39.360 --> 00:04:42.009
directly in front of the
other, and with each step

40
00:04:42.020 --> 00:04:45.589
squats down, picks up one
object from the floor,

41
00:04:45.600 --> 00:04:47.239
and puts it into the cup.

42
00:04:47.640 --> 00:04:50.789
It is important that
the feet remain exactly

43
00:04:50.800 --> 00:04:52.779
on one straight line.

44
00:04:52.820 --> 00:04:56.109
Repeat the exercise three,
four times, scattering the

45
00:04:56.120 --> 00:04:58.739
objects differently each time.

46
00:04:58.780 --> 00:05:02.229
For variety, you can also
scatter objects of different

47
00:05:02.240 --> 00:05:05.209
colors, for example,
yellow, red, and blue.

48
00:05:06.000 --> 00:05:08.729
On the first pass, the child
needs to collect only the

49
00:05:08.740 --> 00:05:12.469
yellow objects, on the second
pass, only the red ones,

50
00:05:12.480 --> 00:05:14.809
and on the third pass,
only the blue ones.

51
00:05:15.280 --> 00:05:18.949
In this way, you make the
task more interesting and

52
00:05:18.960 --> 00:05:21.139
add an extra cognitive load.

53
00:05:22.920 --> 00:05:25.749
We have now gone over
exercises that directly

54
00:05:25.760 --> 00:05:27.659
support learning skills.

55
00:05:27.690 --> 00:05:30.569
And here it is important
to remember, we are not

56
00:05:30.580 --> 00:05:34.319
practicing one specific skill,
such as reading or writing.

57
00:05:34.940 --> 00:05:38.489
We are creating the
neurophysiological foundation

58
00:05:38.500 --> 00:05:40.929
for learning a wide
range of skills.

59
00:05:41.440 --> 00:05:44.559
When the body works in a
coordinated way, it becomes

60
00:05:44.570 --> 00:05:47.509
easier for the brain
to process information.

61
00:05:48.160 --> 00:05:51.449
Continue doing these exercises
regularly, and you will

62
00:05:51.460 --> 00:05:55.399
gradually see changes in how
your child copes with tasks.

63
00:05:56.040 --> 00:05:57.359
See you in the next lesson.

